node.text:
Hiiii!!! ✨ Got ready to film a video and decided to film a reel and show some new favs & try new products!! Here’s the rundown: 

The wet n wild primer is really nice! It sets into the skin, has a cooling sensation at first & had a WEIRD texture lol but ** let it dry down and it creates a smooth canvas. I’ve been loving it with this foundation. 

Speaking of foundation, i was shocked i liked this Kat von d one 💀 i thought it would make me so greasy but it’s been great! Took me forever to try it & i need a different shade but i give it a 8/10

This catrice concealer was dry on me 🥴 didn’t love it. Get the wet n wild incognito concealer if you want a good full coverage one from the drugstore! 

I liked the elf cream bronzer so far! Blended well and was smooth. I thought it looked a touch greasy before setting but i need to play with it a bit more. 

This bh cosmetics bronzer palette is so pretty! I also used it as eyeshadow. It’s deep so if you’re medium/tan like i am- go in with a light hand. 

Juvias place cannot do anything wrong lol i love all of their products and this blush palette is just another thing I’m obsessed with. So pigmented and beautiful colors. 

I tried out some of makeup by Mario’s cosmetics and I’m in LOVE. I thought they would be super sheer or what not based on reviews I’ve seen but woooooowza i love love love the blush, bronzers and highlights. 10/10

I think that covers everything in the video! I did mention a few items on my stories (one that did not work out 😅) so def watch there! Hope you guys are still loving these!! Also if you’ve never listened to niko moon i highly recommend you do if you like this song 🎉 Links for everything are in my story! 

Holy grails in the vid:
@dsmdshop_ sponge
@toofaced peach perfect setting powder

node.text:
Happy fridayyy!!!! Thank the lord it’s the end of the week am i right? 😂😅

I’ve been itching to get ready with this new @jaclynhillcosmetics cosmetics so here we are! Couple details is it’s a limited edition collection (launching 7/13 11am pst) and there’s 4 different products with a few shades in each. I’m going to list my favs in order below with the shade i prefer for myself. Also this is not sponsored I’m just obsessed with new makeup and reels so les go ⬇️

1. Rose drip hydrating oil 🤤 love this for a super glossy lip. It’s thick but not sticky so 10/10. Only need one swipe!
2. Cream bronzer in sandy. This is a thinner formula but dried matte. Perfect for those with oily skin that are scared of cream bronzers because a LOT of the ones on the market have that greasy feeling or don’t last well throughout the day. This is easy to blend & I’ll definitely be using it more often!
3. Putty highlight in star power- this is a great shade for me. Not ashy on my skin and it’s another great lightweight texture. Looks good over my pores and the spots where my rosacea can get a little more textured during a flare up. 
4. Liquid highlighter in lightening. This is sooo nice over foundation. It’s a pretty thin consistency so it’s not going to feel heavy on the skin. This blended really well even though it looked intimidating when first applied 😂 i want to try the shade high gleams mixed with my body lotion to see how it looks! Not glittery which i love. 

So far i like all the products! Nothing i tried where i was thinking oh hell no 😂 definitely snag them if you’re interested! 

I have an IGTV coming soon trying out some new makeup i purchased at Target so stay tuned for that! What makeup are you obsessed with lately?
